==English==
===Etymology===
French [[amunition]], for munition, probably caused by taking la munition as l'amunition.  See  [[Munition]].
[[Category:English nouns which have interacted with their indefinite article]]

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /æm.juˈnɪʃ.ən/

===Noun===
'''ammunition'''

# Articles used in charging [[firearms]] and [[ordnance]] of all kinds; as [[powder]], [[ball]]s, [[shot]], [[shell]]s, [[percussion cap]]s, [[rocket]]s, etc.
# Any stock of missiles, literal or figurative.
<!-- material copied from Webster's Revised Unabridged Dictionary (1913) -->

